==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ethiops
<hw>E"thi*ops</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Ethiop</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Old Chem.)</fld> <def>A black substance;
-- formerly applied to various preparations of a black or very dark
color.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>⟦ae⟧thiops</asp>.]</altsp>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Ethiops martial</b></col> <fld>(Old Chem.)</fld>,
<cd>black oxide of iron.</cd> -- <col><b>Ethiops mineral</b></col>
<fld>(Old Chem.)</fld>, <cd>black sulphide of mercury, obtained by
triturating mercury with sulphur.</cd> -- <col><b>Ethiops per
se</b></col> <fld>(Old Chem.)</fld>, <cd>mercury in finely divided
state, having the appearance of a dark powder, obtained by shaking it up
or by exposure to the air.</cd></cs></p>

<p><ent>Ethmoidal</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Ethmoid</ent>⟦br⟧
